 the bottom of the concept of "environment" in the world religions. How do religions position themselves on the ecological question? What are the foundations of their decisions? And can they make a significant contribution to the current problem and to the enquiries of many people?  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aInterreligiöser Dialog. 4aSchöpfung. 4aUmweltethik. 4aÖkologie.  aInterreligious dialogue.  aLaudato si.  acreation.  aecology.1 aBöttigheimer, Christoph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBöttigheimer, Christoph, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDee, Rabbi Leo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDutton, Yasin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNeril, Rabbi Yonatan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchlögl-Flierl, Kerstin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWidenka, Wenzel M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWidenka, Wenzel Maximilian, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z978311117578208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2023 Englishz978311131928508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2023z9783111318820oZDB-23-DGF0 cEPUBz97831107826910 cprintz978311078231840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311078245540uhttps://www